The calculator uses two parameters: p-ROXI and p-ROXV. The cutoff points for these parameters are 66.7 and 24.0 at 24 hours, and 65.1 and 24.6 at 48 hours, respectively. If both parameters are above their respective cutoff points, the risk of HFNC failure is low. If both parameters are below their respective cutoff points, the risk of HFNC failure is high.

